A mother and son in Illinois had a very lucky escape when a giant sinkhole swallowed their car and were then run over by a truck.

Juanita Pineda, 41, and her son Benjamin Hernandez, 15, were on a paper route at around 3.50am just north of Chicago when their Ford Taurus fell into the 10ft-wide hole last Tuesday.

Benjamin suffered a fractured spine, nose and jaw and lost his front teeth, but their run of atrocious luck didn't end there.

